description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to use your skills in a different way? Would you like to ensure all clinical environments offer the best possible learning experience for our student nurses and midwives and other learners?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 3 Administrator to join the Nursing and Midwifery Clinical Education Team at SWBH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and motivated individual to support our functions in a full-time role. Applicants will require relevant previous experience of an administrative role, be qualified to NVQ level 2 in business administration, and be familiar with the use of Microsoft Office applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work in an administrative role to support the Nursing and Midwifery Clinical Education Team deliver effective and relevant training across the Trust. They will be expected to communicate effectively with student nurses &amp; midwives, nurse associate apprentices, members of trust staff, and staff from affiliated HEI’s to answer queries relating to their learning needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NamePeter HoughtonJob titleLead Education NurseEmail addressswbh.nurse-education@nhs.netTelephone number0121 507 6149&lt;/p&gt;
